"title": "5794: asceticism",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5794",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Rigorous self-denial of bodily pleasures and needs. This can be motivated either by a praiseworthy desire to dedicate oneself completely to God, or by an erroneous belief that the physical body is evil.</p>\n<h2>Types of ascetic practice</h2>\n<h3>The ascetic practice of fasting</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:15-Esth4:16\">EST 4:15–4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:26\">JDG 20:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:11-2Sam1:12\">2SA 1:11–1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer36:5-Jer36:6\">JER 36:5–36:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:37\">LUK 2:37</a></p>\n<h3>The ascetic practice of wearing sackcloth and ashes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:3\">DAN 9:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:27\">1KI 21:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:1\">NEH 9:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:3\">EST 4:3</a></p>\n<h3>The ascetic practice of celibacy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:1\">1CO 7:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:15\">EXO 19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:4\">1SA 21:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:8\">1CO 7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:36-1Cor7:38\">1CO 7:36–7:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:4\">REV 14:4</a></p>\n<h2>People who practised asceticism</h2>\n<h3>The Nazirites and asceticism</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:1-Num6:8\">NUM 6:1–6:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:4-Judg13:5\">JDG 13:4–13:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:17\">JDG 16:17</a></p>\n<h3>John the Baptist and asceticism</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:4\">MAT 3:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:6\">MRK 1:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:18\">MAT 11:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:33\">LUK 7:33</a></p>\n<h3>John's disciples, the Pharisees and asceticism</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:14\">MAT 9:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:18\">MRK 2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:33\">LUK 5:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:12\">LUK 18:12</a></p>\n<h3>The Jews and the ascetic practice of regular fasting</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:26-Lev23:32\">LEV 23:26–23:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:1-Zech7:5\">ZEC 7:1–7:5</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ refuses to enforce ascetic practices</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:18-Mark2:19\">MRK 2:18–2:19</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:14-Matt9:17\">MAT 9:14–9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:34-Luke5:35\">LUK 5:34–5:35</a></p>\n<h2>Ascetic practice symbolises separation from the world and dedication to God</h2>\n<h3>Asceticism as a sign of repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:6-Jonah3:9\">JON 3:6–3:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:6\">1SA 7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:6\">EZR 10:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:13-Joel1:14\">JOL 1:13–1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Asceticism accompanying prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:23\">EZR 8:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:16\">2SA 12:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:4\">NEH 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:23\">ACT 14:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:5\">1CO 7:5</a></p>\n<h3>Ascetic dedication to God's service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:27\">1CO 9:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:8\">DAN 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:12\">MAT 19:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:32-1Cor7:35\">1CO 7:32–7:35</a></p>\n<h2>False asceticism opposed</h2>\n<h3>Rejection of fasting without true repentance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:3-Isa58:7\">ISA 58:3–58:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:12-Joel2:14\">JOL 2:12–2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Condemnation of ostentatious asceticism</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:16-Matt6:18\">MAT 6:16–6:18</a></p>\n<h3>Asceticism not necessary for right worship and conduct</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:20-Col2:23\">COL 2:20–2:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:1-1Tim4:5\">1TI 4:1–4:5</a> <em>Asceticism that is based on a negative view of the material world is rejected.</em></p>",
